Changing the language is considered a configuration change, just like rotating the device or switching the UI from light- to dark mode. Your activity is then recreated and loaded with the appropriate resources.

If you wan&#39;t to handle a configuration change yourself, you need to specify this in your manifest for your activities as stated [here][1].

    &lt;activity android:name=&quot;.MyActivity&quot;
              android:configChanges=&quot;locale&quot;
              android:label=&quot;@string/app_name&quot;&gt;

You can find other valid values for `configChanges` [here][2].


  [1]: https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/resources/runtime-changes#HandlingTheChange
  [2]: https://developer.android.com/guide/topics/manifest/activity-element.html#config

